1. Primary vacancies are proportional to IC coefficients:
$$N_{L1}^p = C\,\alpha_{L1},\qquad N_{L2}^p = C\,\alpha_{L2}\approx 0,\qquad 
N_{L3}^p = C\,\alpha_{L3}.$$

2. Coster–Kronig transfers populate $L_3$ from $L_1$ and $L_2$:
A vacancy in $L_1$ goes to $L_3$ with $f_{13}$ or first to $L_2$ with $f_{12}$ then to $L_3$ with $f_{23}$. Hence
$$N_{L3}^{tot}
= N_{L3}^p 
+ f_{13}\,N_{L1}^p 
+ f_{23}\bigl(N_{L2}^p + f_{12}\,N_{L1}^p\bigr).$$

3. Substitute $N_{L2}^p\approx 0$ and the proportionalities:
$$N_{L3}^{tot}
= C\Bigl[\alpha_{L3} + (f_{13}+f_{12}f_{23})\,\alpha_{L1}\Bigr].$$

4. Measured ratio $\mathcal{R}$ satisfies
$$\mathcal{R}
= \kappa\,\frac{N_{L1}^p}{N_{L3}^{tot}}
= \kappa\,\frac{C\,\alpha_{L1}}
{\,C\bigl[\alpha_{L3} + (f_{13}+f_{12}f_{23})\,\alpha_{L1}\bigr]\!}
= \frac{\kappa\,\alpha_{L1}}
{\alpha_{L3} + (f_{13}+f_{12}f_{23})\,\alpha_{L1}}.$$

5. Let $X=\alpha_{L1}/\alpha_{L3}$. Then
$$\mathcal{R}
= \frac{\kappa\,X}{1 + (f_{13}+f_{12}f_{23})\,X}
\;\Longrightarrow\;
\mathcal{R}\bigl[1+(f_{13}+f_{12}f_{23})X\bigr]
=\kappa\,X$$
$$\Longrightarrow\;
\mathcal{R}
=\;X\bigl[\kappa - \mathcal{R}\,(f_{13}+f_{12}f_{23})\bigr]
\;\;\Longrightarrow\;\;
X=\frac{\mathcal{R}}{\kappa - \mathcal{R}(f_{13}+f_{12}f_{23})}.$$
